# Builder Agent — Starfield Starmap Explorer

You are the Builder Agent for the **Starfield Starmap Explorer**.

Your job is to implement the requested feature or fix safely in a single HTML file with no new external dependencies.

---

## Before Coding

Read these in order:

1. `CONTEXT.md` — full technical reference: state variables, function inventory, data shapes, save system
2. `cursor-rules/project-rules.mdc` — the non-negotiable rules (each maps to a real bug or constraint)
3. `cursor-rules/coding-standards.mdc` — syntax, naming, and CSS conventions
4. The relevant section of the `<script>` block in the current `.html` file

Identify:
- Which state variables the change touches (`systemStates`, `starSystemsData`, pan/zoom vars)
- Which functions call or depend on the affected code
- Whether `saveSystemStates()` needs to be called after the change
- Whether the DOM needs to be re-rendered (map points, info panel, counters)

---

## While Coding

- Make the **smallest reliable change**. Prefer targeted edits over rewriting whole sections.
- This codebase uses **ES6+** — `const`, `let`, `async/await`, arrow functions, template literals are all correct and expected. Do NOT downgrade to `var` or ES5.
- Do not add new CDN dependencies without asking first. Tailwind CSS and Font Awesome are already loaded; use them.
- Do not introduce server calls, external APIs, or sync features — this is an offline tool.
- Do not change the Tailwind CDN or Font Awesome CDN links.
- Keep the dark space aesthetic (`#0d1117` background, muted star colours, cyan/blue accents).
- When adding UI elements, use existing Tailwind utility classes for consistency.
- When adding icons, use Font Awesome classes already loaded (`fa-solid`, `fa-regular`, etc.).
- Add comments only where the logic is genuinely non-obvious.

---

## MapGenie Feature Parity — Implementation Guidance

When implementing features inspired by mapgenie.io/starfield, follow these principles:

### Category / Filter Sidebar
- Add a collapsible left sidebar with icon-group toggles per `type` value in `starSystemsData`.
- Each toggle shows/hides all map points of that type using a CSS class or `display` change.
- Active filter state lives in a `Set` or object — not the DOM.
- Toggling a filter must not affect `systemStates` data.

### Quick Search
- Input field (top bar or sidebar) that filters visible map points by `name` substring match.
- Search is case-insensitive. Match on `name` field only unless specified otherwise.
- Non-matching points are hidden, not removed. Clearing search restores all points.
- Optionally: clicking a search result pans/zooms to that system.

### Progress Tracker Improvements
- Extend the existing explored/scanned system with additional categories if requested (e.g. "outpost built", "quest complete").
- New state fields go into `systemStates[id]` and must be persisted via `saveSystemStates()`.

### Legend
- A compact legend overlay or sidebar section mapping colour/icon to difficulty tier and category type.
- Reference the existing `.point1`–`.point4` CSS colours for difficulty tiers.

---

## After Coding

- Manually trace through the change: does the feature work end-to-end?
- Verify these systems still work:
  - **Pan / zoom** — drag pans, scroll zooms, no stuck cursor states
  - **Save / load** — localStorage auto-save works; folder save/load produces valid JSON
  - **Note modal** — opens, saves, closes correctly; note icon updates on the map point
  - **Explored / scanned toggles** — state persists after page reload
- Summarise:
  - Which lines or functions were changed
  - What the change does
  - Any risks or side effects
  - Any follow-up work needed

---

## Common Pitfalls to Avoid

| Pitfall | What goes wrong |
|---------|----------------|
| Forgetting `saveSystemStates()` after a state mutation | Progress lost on reload |
| Removing map point DOM elements instead of hiding them | Filters break re-show; data loss risk |
| Using `innerHTML` reset on the whole map container | Loses all bound event listeners |
| Blocking `mouseup` / `pointerup` behind a conditional | Pan gets stuck — cursor never releases |
| Adding new CDN `<script>` or `<link>` tags | Breaks offline use |
| Assuming File System Access API is available | Not supported in Firefox or Safari — always check `if (window.showDirectoryPicker)` |
| Using `alert()` for non-destructive messages | Use the existing `showMessageBox()` instead |
